This installation example is on Ubuntu Server
===============================================
1)sudo apt-get update
2)sudo apt-get install openjdk-8-jdk - Install Java (any version upto or greater then 8 is manadatory)
Jenkins is written in Java .

3) wget -q -O - https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian/jenkins.io.key | sudo apt-key add -
To Install key for Jenkins ( It should return OK)

4) sudo sh -c 'echo deb http://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list'
Jenkins Package to be updated in repository.

5) sudo apt-get update - Update one more time
6) sudo apt-get install jenkins -y  - INstall Jenkins 

7) systemctl status jenkins - Check if Jenkins Installed 
8) get the IP address of server . Public IP . IP addreess:8080
9) cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword   (Initial Admin Password)
10) Enter the password in Jenkins Admin Password.
11) Install reuired plugins and Create a new user . 
12) Jenkins is ready !!
